# Add "Open with Antigravity" to Context Menu (Silent Mode)

This plan updates/registers the context menu shortcut for Antigravity. It uses a hidden PowerShell window to execute the application, ensuring no terminal windows flash when the user selects the option.

## Proposed Changes

### Registry Customization

We will create a registry import file (`.reg`) to define the context menu items for files, directories, and the directory background.

#### [NEW] [antigravity_context_menu.reg](file:///C:/Users/user/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/antigravity_context_menu.reg)
Detailed registry keys to be added:
- `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\*\shell\OpenWithAntigravity`: Context menu for all files.
- `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\OpenWithAntigravity`: Context menu for folders.
- `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\Background\shell\OpenWithAntigravity`: Context menu for the background (empty space) within a folder.

Each key will:
- Set the display name to "Open with Antigravity".
- Set the icon to the Antigravity icon.
- Set the command to: `powershell.exe -WindowStyle Hidden -Command "& 'C:\Users\user\AppData\Local\Programs\Antigravity\Antigravity.exe' '%1'"` (or `%V` for background).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run `reg query` commands to verify the keys are present and contain the expected silent PowerShell command.
    ```powershell
    reg query "HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\*\shell\OpenWithAntigravity\command" /ve
    reg query "HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\OpenWithAntigravity\command" /ve
    reg query "HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\Background\shell\OpenWithAntigravity\command" /ve
    ```

### Manual Verification
- **File Context**: Right-click a file and select "Open with Antigravity". Verify the app opens and NO terminal window appears.
- **Folder Context**: Right-click a folder and select "Open with Antigravity". Verify the app opens for that directory.
- **Background Context**: Right-click in the empty space of a folder and select "Open with Antigravity". Verify the app opens for the current directory.
